          <p class="mb-4" style="color: var(--text-soft);">Where I would give Howdens a slight edge is in the consistency and robustness of its trade-facing ranges — the Tewkesbury and Greenwich in particular have a well-established reputation among fitters for reliable construction and consistent tolerances. Magnet's quality is also good, but the brand positions itself slightly more as a design-led consumer product, which can mean more variation in how well specific ranges handle the practicalities of installation.</p>

