          { q: "Is DIY Kitchens actually flat-pack?", a: "No. Despite the name, DIY Kitchens supplies rigid, pre-assembled carcasses direct from their Yorkshire factory. The name refers to the direct-to-consumer buying model, not the product format. Units install at the same speed as any other rigid kitchen." },
          { q: "Is DIY Kitchens better quality than Wren?", a: "At equivalent price points, DIY Kitchens' specification often exceeds entry-to-mid Wren, because the factory-direct model puts more budget into the product. Wren's premium ranges are well constructed, but they carry a brand and showroom premium. Compare specific specifications rather than brand names." },
          { q: "Can an independent fitter install a DIY Kitchens kitchen?", a: "Yes. DIY Kitchens does not require a specific installation service. The rigid pre-assembled units are standard in format and any experienced kitchen fitter will install them efficiently." },
          { q: "How long does DIY Kitchens take to deliver?", a: "DIY Kitchens manufactures to order, which can mean slightly longer lead times than Wren in some cases. Current lead times vary with demand — check directly with the company at the time of ordering. Both typically deliver to the home in a single bulk delivery." },
